cs.CL, cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.SOC, cs.LG 

This paper involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques to learn name embeddings and classify nationalities based on communication patterns. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves machine learning and data mining techniques to analyze large datasets, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing). The paper also has sociological implications, which could place it in cs.SOC (Computers and Society). Finally, the paper involves the development of a new representation for encoding gender, ethnicity, and nationality, which could also place it in cs.LG (Machine Learning).
